spanishExample: Quiero traerte un regalo la próxima semana.
englishTranslation: I want to bring you a gift next week.

spanishExample: Siempre traemos todo lo que necesitamos.
englishTranslation: We always bring everything we need.

spanishExample: Trajo el plato tardísimo.
englishTranslation: He brought the dish super late.

spanishExample: Tráelo, aunque él no quiere que lo traigas.
englishTranslation: Bring it, even though he doesn’t want you to bring it.

spanishExample: No puedes traerme dinero.
englishTranslation: You can’t bring me money.

spanishExample: Va a traer la computadora después.
englishTranslation: She is going to bring the computer afterwards.

spanishExample: Ojalá traigan vasos.
englishTranslation: Hopefully they'll bring glasses.

spanishExample: Si trae la llave, entraremos.
englishTranslation: If he brings the key, we’ll go in.

spanishExample: Definitivamente traerá su reloj.
englishTranslation: He will definitely bring his watch.

spanishExample: La cerradura está completamente bien, no necesito que traiga una nueva.
englishTranslation: The lock is completely fine, I don’t need him to bring a new one.

spanishExample: ¡Traiga esas sillas!
englishTranslation: (Formal) Bring those chairs!

spanishExample: Quiere que traiga algo, porque no he traído nada.
englishTranslation: He wants me to bring something, because I haven’t brought anything.

spanishExample: Traigan eso enseguida.
englishTranslation: (Plural) Bring that immediately.

spanishExample: Siempre traigo un tenedor y un cuchillo para comer afuera.
englishTranslation: I always bring a fork and a knife to eat outside.

spanishExample: Tienes que traerlo ahora, date prisa.
englishTranslation: You have to bring it now, hurry up.

spanishExample: ¿No lo trajiste? Qué bueno que yo lo traje.
englishTranslation: You didn’t bring it? How nice that I brought it.

spanishExample: Tráeme el café, por favor.
englishTranslation: Bring me the coffee, please.

spanishExample: Trae dos perritos para que podamos jugar.
englishTranslation: Bring two doggies so we can play.

spanishExample: ¿Qué traes? // Ellos traen algo más.
englishTranslation: What are you bringing? // They are bringing something else.

spanishExample: Traeré la comida porque ellos no la trajeron.
englishTranslation: I’ll bring the food, because they didn’t bring it.

spanishExample: No traigas eso, nosotros ya lo trajimos.
englishTranslation: Don’t bring that, we already brought it.
